---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title="Territorium - Territorial resilience and return"
  description="Territorium advises on territory transactions, natural capital and turnkey restoration to turn land into resilience, return and legacy."
>

  <header class="hero" id="hero-carousel">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <span class="hero__eyebrow">Territorium Capital · Advisory & Restoration</span>
      <h1 class="hero__title fade-in" id="carousel-title">
        Territories, natural capital and turnkey restoration
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__subtitle fade-in" id="carousel-subtitle">
        We advise on rural asset transactions and design restoration projects that turn territory into resilience, return and legacy.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__actions">
        <a href="#contacto" class="hero__cta">Speak to an expert</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="service-finder reveal" aria-label="Main needs">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="service-finder__label">What you need</span>
        <div class="service-finder__grid">
          <a href="#territorios" class="service-finder__item">
            <small>01</small>
            <span>Buy or sell high ecological value territory</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#servicios" class="service-finder__item">
            <small>02</small>
            <span>Restore and manage</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#vision" class="service-finder__item">
            <small>03</small>
            <span>Understand ecological value</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#clientes" class="service-finder__item">
            <small>04</small>
            <span>Invest in natural capital</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="manifesto-section reveal">
      <div class="manifesto-section__image">
        <img src="/imagenes/territorio-legado.jpg" alt="Natural landscape managed by Territorium">
      </div>
      <div class="manifesto-section__copy">
        <span class="section-kicker">Rooted in land</span>
        <h2>We are born from it, live from it and return to it.</h2>
        <p>
          Food, history and life itself emerge from land. It is the legacy where
          the next generations will live and the future of our species will be
          shaped.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="porque" class="problem-section reveal">
      <div class="container editorial-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="section-kicker">Why Territorium</span>
          <h2>The value of land is no longer measured only by what it produces.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="editorial-copy">
          <p>
            For decades, territory has been valued mainly by its agricultural,
            livestock, forestry, urban or extractive productivity.
          </p>
          <p>
            Yet variables such as biodiversity, ecological connectivity, climate
            resilience, water, soil, landscape, tree cover and restoration
            potential hold strategic value that many owners, companies and public
            bodies are not yet activating.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="territorios" class="estate-section reveal">
      <div class="estate-section__content">
        <div class="estate-section__header">
          <div>
            <span class="section-kicker">Territories and turnkey restoration</span>
            <h2>Transactions on territories with high ecological value.</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            Acquisition, restoration, management and sale with a clear thesis
            around patrimonial value, biodiversity, water, landscape and natural
            capital.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="estate-section__note">
          <strong>Territorium model</strong>
          <span>From rural asset to investable, restored and defensible territory before buyers, partners or investment committees.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="transaction-flow">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Acquire</h3>
            <p>Origination and valuation of territories with ecological and patrimonial potential.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Restore</h3>
            <p>Turnkey project with budget, indicators and technical monitoring.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Manage</h3>
            <p>Activation of biodiversity, water, landscape and climate resilience.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Sell</h3>
            <p>Value thesis prepared for qualified buyers and investors.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="restauracion" class="restoration-section reveal">
      <div class="container restoration-section__header">
        <span class="section-kicker">Before and after</span>
        <h2>Restoration becomes clear when territory changes.</h2>
        <p>
          Restoration is not cosmetic. It increases resilience, ecological value
          and future optionality. Drag the line to compare the initial condition
          with the outcome of a project designed to recover water, vegetation,
          biodiversity and landscape value.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="container restoration-cinema">
        <div class="restoration-compare" data-compare>
          <img class="restoration-compare__image" src="/imagenes/restauracion-despues.png" alt="Territory before the restoration project">
          <div class="restoration-compare__after" data-compare-after>
            <img class="restoration-compare__image" src="/imagenes/restauracion-antes.jpg" alt="Territory after the restoration project">
          </div>
          <div class="restoration-compare__handle" data-compare-handle aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <input class="restoration-compare__range" data-compare-range type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" aria-label="Compare before and after restoration">
          <span class="restoration-compare__label restoration-compare__label--before">Before</span>
          <span class="restoration-compare__label restoration-compare__label--after">After</span>
          <div class="restoration-compare__caption">
            <strong>Degradation → resilience</strong>
            <span>Water, vegetation, habitat and territorial value.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container--narrow section-intro reveal">
      <div class="section-intro__block">
        <h2 class="section-intro__heading">
          We combine the wisdom of land with the technology of the future.
        </h2>
        <p class="section-intro__body">
          We combine environmental science, satellite imagery, data analysis and
          nature-based solutions to audit your territory.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="divider-icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="divider-icon__line"></div>
        <svg class="divider-icon__svg" viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none">
          <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="19" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          <line x1="20" y1="29" x2="20" y2="16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <path d="M20 22 C16 20 13 16 15 12 C17 15 19 18 20 22Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" fill="none"/>
          <path d="M20 19 C24 17 27 13 25 9 C23 12 21 15 20 19Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" fill="none"/>
          <path d="M13 29 Q20 27 27 29" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="divider-icon__line"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-intro__block">
        <h2 class="section-intro__heading">
          We turn ecosystem data into a
          <span class="text-accent">clear financial balance.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-intro__body">
          Enabling strategic decisions based on the real value of your asset.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="servicios" class="section-axes reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <span class="section-kicker section-kicker--light">Our lines of work</span>
          <h2>From territorial diagnosis to value creation.</h2>
          <p>
            A methodology to acquire, value, restore and manage territories
            with ecological, patrimonial and financial judgement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="axes-showcase">
          <article class="axes-feature">
            <span class="axes-feature__eyebrow">Territorium Method</span>
            <h3>We turn territory into a defensible investment thesis.</h3>
            <p>
              We measure ecological potential, translate its variables into
              patrimonial value and design a roadmap to activate the asset:
              acquire, restore, manage or sell with greater clarity.
            </p>
            <a href="mailto:blanca@territorium.capital" class="axes-feature__cta">Discuss my territory</a>
          </article>

          <div class="axes-grid" aria-label="Territorium lines of work">
            <article class="card-axis">
              <span class="card-axis__number">01</span>
              <div class="card-axis__content">
                <h3 class="card-axis__name">Territories</h3>
                <p class="card-axis__tag">Acquisition and sale</p>
                <p class="card-axis__body">Sourcing, valuation and preparation of territories with high ecological value.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="card-axis">
              <span class="card-axis__number">02</span>
              <div class="card-axis__content">
                <h3 class="card-axis__name">Management</h3>
                <p class="card-axis__tag">Territorial decision</p>
                <p class="card-axis__body">Measurement of biodiversity, water, landscape and resilience to prioritize action.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="card-axis">
              <span class="card-axis__number">03</span>
              <div class="card-axis__content">
                <h3 class="card-axis__name">Capital</h3>
                <p class="card-axis__tag">Value thesis</p>
                <p class="card-axis__body">Financial reading of natural capital to support opportunity, risk and price.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="card-axis">
              <span class="card-axis__number">04</span>
              <div class="card-axis__content">
                <h3 class="card-axis__name">Restoration</h3>
                <p class="card-axis__tag">Turnkey delivery</p>
                <p class="card-axis__body">Design, execution and monitoring of restoration projects with measurable impact.</p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="vision" class="advantage-section reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading section-heading--left">
          <span class="section-kicker">Market insight</span>
          <h2>Territorial research for investment-grade decisions.</h2>
          <p>
            The quality of a transaction starts before the site visit. We analyse
            the asset as a real estate advisory firm would, while also
            incorporating natural capital, restoration and climate resilience.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="urban-analysis">
          <div class="urban-analysis__image">
            <img src="/imagenes/territorio-urbano-analisis.jpg" alt="Green cover analysis in urban territory">
          </div>
          <div class="urban-analysis__copy">
            <span>Urban and peri-urban analysis</span>
            <h3>We measure green infrastructure in urban territory as well.</h3>
            <p>
              Reading vegetation cover, ecological connectivity and opportunity
              areas helps identify where an urban environment can gain
              resilience, environmental value and territorial quality.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resilience-metric">
          <span>Core resilience metric</span>
          <h3>The more biodiverse a territory is, the more resilient it becomes against climate events.</h3>
          <p>
            Biodiversity reduces vulnerability, improves the ecosystem’s ability
            to recover and increases the ecological value of the asset. More
            resilience means lower territorial risk, higher potential return and
            a more defensible investment thesis.
          </p>
          <div class="resilience-flow" aria-label="Biodiversity, resilience, return and ecological value">
            <strong>Biodiversity</strong>
            <strong>Climate resilience</strong>
            <strong>Return</strong>
            <strong>Ecological value</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="advantage-grid">
          <article class="advantage-item">
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Valuation</h3>
            <p>Real estate, environmental and patrimonial reading of the asset to support price, potential and risk.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="advantage-item">
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Opportunity</h3>
            <p>Identification of uses, restoration, compensation, biodiversity, water, landscape and ESG theses.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="advantage-item">
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Execution</h3>
            <p>Technical and financial roadmap to move from acquisition to restored project.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="why-us-section reveal">
      <div class="container why-us-grid">
        <div class="why-us-intro">
          <span class="section-kicker">Why us</span>
          <h2>We do not simply intermediate territory. We make it investable, restorable and defensible.</h2>
          <p>
            Our difference lies in combining the transactional perspective of a
            real estate advisory firm with environmental science, natural capital
            and execution capacity on the ground.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="why-us-list">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>From ecological data to patrimonial value</h3>
            <p>We translate biodiversity, water, soil, landscape and climate resilience into buy, sell and investment decisions.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Turnkey restoration, not just recommendations</h3>
            <p>We design the project, budget it, coordinate execution and provide technical traceability for reporting and monitoring.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Specialists in rural assets with natural potential</h3>
            <p>We do not treat territory as a generic real estate asset: we analyse its ecological, productive, regulatory and patrimonial capacity.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>A clear thesis for owners and investors</h3>
            <p>We build a value narrative that helps defend price, risk, opportunity and legacy before buyers, partners or committees.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="science-section reveal">
      <div class="container science-grid">
        <div class="science-card">
          <span class="section-kicker">Scientific credibility</span>
          <h2>Collaboration with Universidad Politécnica de Madrid.</h2>
          <p>
            We integrate technical and academic knowledge into territorial
            assessment, ecological land analysis and the design of traceable
            restoration projects.
          </p>
          <div class="science-method">
            <span>Environmental science</span>
            <span>Territorial analysis</span>
            <span>Biodiversity indicators</span>
            <span>Investment decision</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a href="https://www.upm.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="science-logo" aria-label="Universidad Politécnica de Madrid">
          <img src="imagenes/aliado_1.jpeg" alt="Universidad Politécnica de Madrid logo">
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="clientes" class="audience-section reveal">
      <div class="container editorial-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="section-kicker">Who we serve</span>
          <h2>Territories built for legacy, return and the future.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-list">
          <article>
            <h3>Large landowners</h3>
            <p>Families and private owners seeking to pass on a more valuable, resilient and profitable legacy.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>Investment funds and family offices</h3>
            <p>Investors seeking to optimise rural assets under rigorous ESG criteria.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>Companies and corporations</h3>
            <p>Companies that need to offset environmental impact through local, real and traceable projects.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>Public administrations</h3>
            <p>Entities requiring advanced and sustainable management of forests, estates and public natural spaces.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="partners-section reveal" aria-label="Partners">
      <div class="partners-grid">
        <a href="https://www.upm.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="partner-item">
          <img src="imagenes/aliado_1.jpeg" alt="Universidad Politécnica de Madrid logo" class="partner-logo">
        </a>

        <a href="https://www.wildlife-estates.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="partner-item">
          <img src="imagenes/aliado_2.jpeg" alt="Logo Wildlife Estates" class="partner-logo">
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

</Layout>

<script>
  const slides = [
    {
      image: "url('/imagenes/fondo-1.jpg')",
      title: "Territories with natural value<br/>for investors and owners",
      subtitle: "Advisory for rural asset transactions, valuation and activation."
    },
    {
      image: "url('/imagenes/fondo-2.jpg')",
      title: "Turnkey ecological<br/>restoration",
      subtitle: "Design, execution, monitoring and reporting to transform territory with rigour."
    },
    {
      image: "url('/imagenes/fondo-3.jpg')",
      title: "Natural capital<br/>turned into patrimonial strategy",
      subtitle: "We integrate science, data and financial judgement to multiply territorial value."
    }
  ];

  let currentIndex = 0;
  const heroElement = document.getElementById('hero-carousel') as HTMLElement;
  const titleElement = document.getElementById('carousel-title') as HTMLElement;
  const subtitleElement = document.getElementById('carousel-subtitle') as HTMLElement;

  function changeSlide() {
    currentIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % slides.length;
    const next = slides[currentIndex];

    if (titleElement && subtitleElement && heroElement) {
      titleElement.classList.remove('fade-in');
      subtitleElement.classList.remove('fade-in');
      titleElement.classList.add('fade-out');
      subtitleElement.classList.add('fade-out');

      setTimeout(() => {
        heroElement.style.backgroundImage =
          `linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(10,20,32,0.82), rgba(10,20,32,0.48) 48%, rgba(10,20,32,0.18)), ${next.image}`;
        titleElement.innerHTML = next.title;
        subtitleElement.textContent = next.subtitle;
        titleElement.classList.remove('fade-out');
        subtitleElement.classList.remove('fade-out');
        titleElement.classList.add('fade-in');
        subtitleElement.classList.add('fade-in');
      }, 600);
    }
  }

  setInterval(changeSlide, 6000);

  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const checkVisibility = (entries: IntersectionObserverEntry[], observer: IntersectionObserver) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add("active");
          observer.unobserve(entry.target);
        }
      });
    };

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(checkVisibility, {
      root: null,
      rootMargin: "0px",
      threshold: 0.1
    });

    const elementsToReveal = document.querySelectorAll(".reveal");
    elementsToReveal.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));

    const compare = document.querySelector("[data-compare]") as HTMLElement | null;
    const range = document.querySelector("[data-compare-range]") as HTMLInputElement | null;
    const after = document.querySelector("[data-compare-after]") as HTMLElement | null;
    const handle = document.querySelector("[data-compare-handle]") as HTMLElement | null;

    const setComparePosition = (value: string) => {
      if (!after || !handle) return;
      after.style.clipPath = `inset(0 ${100 - Number(value)}% 0 0)`;
      handle.style.left = `${value}%`;
    };

    if (compare && range && after && handle) {
      setComparePosition(range.value);
      range.addEventListener("input", () => setComparePosition(range.value));
    }

  });
</script>

<style>
  .hero {
    background-image: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(10,20,32,0.82), rgba(10,20,32,0.48) 48%, rgba(10,20,32,0.18)), url('/imagenes/fondo-1.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    transition: background-image 1.2s ease-in-out;
    will-change: background-image;
  }

  .hero__title,
  .hero__subtitle {
    transition: opacity 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1),
                transform 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    will-change: opacity, transform;
  }

  .hero__subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .hero__actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .hero__cta--primary {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-white);
    padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .fade-in  { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  .fade-out { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }

  .service-finder {
    background: transparent;
    border-bottom: 0;
    margin-top: -3.5rem;
    padding-inline: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 5;
  }

  .service-finder .container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
    align-items: stretch;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(24, 43, 73, 0.12);
    max-width: 72rem;
    padding: var(--space-5, 1.25rem);
  }

  .service-finder__label {
    align-self: start;
    color: var(--color-indigo);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .service-finder__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-border);
  }

  .service-finder__item {
    background: var(--color-white);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    min-height: 84px;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .service-finder__item:hover {
    background: #f7f4ee;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .service-finder__item small {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  }

  .service-finder__item span {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-indigo);
    font-family: 'Alice', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.4vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .section-kicker {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .section-kicker--light {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
  }

  .section-heading {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-heading--left {
    margin-inline: 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .section-heading h2,
  .editorial-grid h2,
  .manifesto-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-3xl), 5vw, var(--text-5xl));
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .section-heading p,
  .editorial-copy p,
  .manifesto-section p {
    color: var(--color-body);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .section-axes .section-heading p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
  }

  .estate-section {
    background: #ede8dd;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .estate-section__content {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding: clamp(var(--space-12), 8vw, var(--space-20)) var(--space-6);
  }

  .estate-section__header {
    align-items: end;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(280px, 0.75fr);
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  .estate-section__content h2 {
    color: var(--color-indigo);
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-3xl), 5vw, var(--text-5xl));
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.08;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .estate-section__header p {
    color: var(--color-body);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 34rem;
  }

  .estate-section__note {
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-indigo);
    color: var(--color-white);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(180px, 0.35fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
